items.text: The best prawn mee, fantastic soup!
Mee rebus. I was unimpressed with my serving from the corner Malay stall (no name). Overly thick sauce, with undetectable shrimp taste or fragrance. For $3, I got 1 hard boiled egg
Pig organ soup, fish soup, braised duck rice, nasi Padang and fruit stalls are all really fresh.
Try the herbal chicken soup at stall 31!
Duck! Really really good.
If you feel like splurging, treat yourself to a 12 SGD pork ribs and prawn mee soup. I had mine with the noodles on the side and was one happy camper.
I only come here for Big Prawn Mee and nothing else =)
Was quite disappointed with this Cheng Tng because it tastes like lychee instead..
Halp lol zzzz
Best char kway teow and very tasty pigs organ soup.
Wantan mee. The hero item fr Xin Fei Fei Wanton Noodle #01-06 is the wantan itself. Well-made, generous fillings. For ur WTM, order either fried or boiled (or mixed!). Noodles r 'q' (chewy) too
Char kway teow! But lady boss has attitude prob
Fd is bt fantastic but edible
Must-try 18 Zion Rd fried kway teow!
Where do i start? Western food is da bomb, pig organ soup, Cheng ting, fried Kwai teow...
Prawn noodle soup to die for.....
Sugar cane and green apple from Chun Kee Fresh Fruit Juice is nice. Also try sugar cane and beet root.
Carrot cake was nice but not something I prefer. Maybe should try the famous wanton and char kuah teow next time
Definitely the carrot cake
Char kway teow, carrot cake n western is good!
best fried kway teow ever!
Fried Kway Teow
Steam fish is great!!!
Xin Fei Fei Wanton Noodle - fantastic wanton noodles!
Must eat chong pang huat chicken wings very juicy n fresh. My 1st try
Boon tong kee braised duck rice and Kway chap - cheap and awesome. The black rice is so fragrant n the duck so tender
Kway Chap wif Duck meat... A Must-Try!!! (^_~)/b
Not a breakfast spot. Only kopi, bak kut teh & Muslim foodstalls open for biz
Seng Huat Western Food is excellent
The chay kuay teow is fantastic, and the portion is huge!
18 Zion rd fried Kway tiow( at the entrance) is delicious!!
You need to get the Kway Chap here!
Wide variety of good food. Highly recommended!
Very conveniently located opposite great world city.
Most of the stalls serve very good food. The famous stalls are the prawn noodle and the char kway teow. Both have long lines. For those who want something healthy, the fish soup is especially good.
The floor here is really good quality and very hard.
Chong Pang chicken wings!  Can't stop eating ...
Riverside Good Food serves the best oyster omelette in Singapore!
Try the fried kway teow and pig innards soup
Expensive and salty prawn noodles
Claypot rice is the best! Esp the fish!!
Best carrot cake in town at Lau Goh Chye Thow Kway!
Hock Heng Fish Soup is a must try here! Only opens from Thurs thru Sunday!

Cheng tng: Stall 32 (Mohamed Sultan Rd Hot & Cold Cheng Tng) selling same recipe since his father's time. Opens Tue, Thu & Sat fr 12pm-ish to 9pm cos stall owner says he's operating it single-handedly
Decent Yong tau foo if you catch the right items at the right time
Chicken rice, wonton, char kway teow.
I am not a wanton mee person but I find their wanton mee is really gd. Worth the queue! Xin fei fei wanton me
Affordable but mediocre street hawker.
Char Kway tiao so so only! Adam prawn mee, Satay beehoon & western food is my all time fav. there!!
Try the char kway teow, very shiok!!
Fantastic chicken rice at stall 22.
Prawn mee still the best! $8 most value with 3 big ones plus pork ribs.

Must have here are shark head from tian jin seafood, carrot cake from lau goh and dragonfruit juice from chun kee! :D
Yummy Noo Cheng prawn mee..yummy char kuay teow..BBQ wings.
Must try the Laksa, so shiok! :)
BBQ chicken wings home order. Chong Pang 1 (stall 7) free delivery for orders over SGD 30. Wings $1.30, whole spring chicken $9, Otah (big) $1, Otah (small) $0.40. Call 83303996
All the foods here are fantastic! Can't miss them!
$10 Big Prawn Noodles stall near the toilet, Kway Chap with Duck Rice stall, and Chye Tow Kway stall are the best! Chye Tow Kway hawker is deaf, so just point at what you want on the counter-top!
Clean hawker centre that serves up terrific food in almost every stall!
The Cheng Teng at the corner store is fantastic!
8 before me
Corner Char Kway Teow's standard dropped.
Must try: the fish soup stall next to cheng tang! Love the friendly auntie and yummy soup!
Prawn noodle n Wanton noodle.
Prawn noodles, char kway teow, mixed pork soup, yong tau hu
The prawn noodles n char quay tiao ... Still e same ... Awesome!!!!
来早了 很多没开门 不过还是很赞
Dessert stall selling aballing with beancurd & soya bean milk.
Prawn mee standard drop liao don't listen to ppl who tell you otherwise. Hock Heng fish soup is the best. Xiu fei fei wanton noodle damn gd shuijiao, too. Chongpang chicken & pork satay sedap, too!
The Cheng tng is fantastic but the attitude of the hawker's attitude is NOT
Dont bother to try any dessert from both stall. Quantity too little for the price.. one of the stall cheng teng look like this.

Noo Cheng big prawn noodles + Cheng Teng! Note that the Cheng Teng stall is only opened on Tuesday, Thursday and Saturday!
Best BKT in Singapore IMHO

Duck rice is superb, amazing, definitely worth dropping by for.
Boon Tong Kee Kway Chap and Braised Duck!
Die Die Must Try Char Kway Tiao ! Simply Soul Appetizing !

There's a Boon Tong Kee for duck too?? Try their $4 set meal. The chilli goes very well with the duck rice!
Boon Tong Kee Braised Duck Rice looked good, but the duck meat tasted bland. do not want again.
Foo Kee Famous Deepfried Toufu & Taupok - sinfully good veg fritters!
Yes I know ;)
Cheesy tofu from Foo Kee Famous Deepfried is tofutastic

Delicions Noo Cheng prawn mee! Soup always deserves a 2nd helping..
Nice CKT at corner stall 18
The prawn noodles SOUP is fantastic must try
Wanton Mee is a must try! ;)
Hock Heng Fish Soup opens only from Thu-Sun. Friendly, generous, yummy! :)
Must eat. Char kueh teow, prawn noodles, herbal soup, duck noodle/porridge. ^_^

Lau goh chye thow kuay is excellent
Dont miss the Char Kway Teoh of stall No. 18
Try the char kway teow and prawn noodles.
trying to get Spiced up
No 24 Boon Tong Kee Kway Chap and Braised Duck. Really superb! Must try.
Satay, Oyster Omelet/Omelette & desserts must EAT :D  (Y)

Must try Kway Teow.

char kway teow, I go to stall 18
